\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{1}(\boldsymbol{x})=3x_{1}+x_{2}$
\end_inset

, let 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{2}(\boldsymbol{x})=x_{1}+2x_{2}$
\end_inset

, and let
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
X=\{\boldsymbol{x}\in\mathbb{R}^{2}\mid x_{1}+x_{2}\leq7,0\leq x_{1}\leq5,0\leq x_{2}\leq5\}.
\]

\end_inset

For this problem we consider the following BOP:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\text{maximize} & \quad[f_{1}(\boldsymbol{x}),f_{2}(\boldsymbol{x})]\\
\text{subject to} & \quad\boldsymbol{x}\in X.
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Use any method or software of your choice to answer the following questions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Find the ideal point for this BOP and use it as the reference point in parts
 b), c), d) below.
 
\end_layout

